X
0,1,2, \ldots n
\binom{n}{0}, \binom{n}{1}, \ldots, \binom{n}{n}
\mathbb{P}(X)= \binom{n}{x}/2^n
\begin{split} \mathbb{E}(X)  &= \binom{n}{1}/2^n+ \binom{n}{2}/2^n + \ldots + \binom{n}{n}/2^n\\  &= \frac{\binom{n}{1} + \binom{n}{2} + \ldots + \binom{n}{n}}{2^n}\\  &=  \frac{n \cdot 2^{n-1}}{2^n}\\  &= n/2 \end{split} 
\mathbb{E}(X^2)  = \binom{1}{1}/2^n+ \binom{4}{2}/2^n + \ldots 
n/4
 \mathbb{E}[X] = \sum_{k=1}^n \binom{n}{k} k /2^n = \frac{1}{2^n} \sum_{k=1}^n \binom{n}{k} k 
 \mathbb{E}[X^2] = \frac{1}{2^n} \sum_{k=1}^n \binom{n}{k} k^2 
